{"word":"οὐρεύς","slug":"οὐρεύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75980\" key=\"ou)reu/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">οὐρεύς</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ῆος</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion.\">Ion.</a></gram> </gramGrp> for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀρεύς</foreign> (q. v.): in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:50\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.50</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:10:84\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">10.84</biblScope> </bibl> it has been taken as, <sense id=\"n75980.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">=</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">οὖρος, φύλαξ</ref></xr>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a guard, warder</tr_>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg034.perseus-grc1:1461a:10\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Po.\">Po.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1461a10</biblScope> </bibl>; but it may well mean <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">mules</tr_> here, as in other places, and the Sch. give both explanations.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}